How can I fix this Java code to avoid a NullPointerException? "public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String name = null;
        System.out.println(name.length());
    }
}"

answer:
In the code above, the instance variable name is null. Since Java is a null-safe language, the call to length() on name results in a NullPointerException.  You can fix this by initializing name to an empty string:

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String name = "";
        System.out.println(name.length());
    }
}

